 Jul 06 2017
HARTMANN partners with Dr. Donna Bliss for Product Workshop at NADONA’s 30th LTC National Conference
HARTMANN partners with Dr. Donna Bliss for an in-depth product workshop to discuss the assessment and prevention of IASD in nursing home residents at the NADONA LTC national conference in Lake Buena Vista, Flo. The workshop is scheduled for Monday, July 17th at noon.


 



2017-06-02
HARTMANN USA now offering Formaldehyde-donor free adult wipes
HARTMANN is committed to providing high quality service and products that support the daily needs of long-term care residents and professional caregivers. With this commitment in mind, we have updated our pre-moistened adult washcloth formula to complement our extensive portfolio of skin-friendly incontinence products.


 



2017-03-27
HARTMANN USA expands compression portfolio with TwoPress® 2 and Co-Lastic® Sterile
HARTMANN USA is pleased to announce the launch of two new compression products: Co-Lastic® Sterile, a skin-friendly cohesive bandage that can be used in a variety of clinical settings, including the sterile field; and Two Press® 2, a two-layer compression bandaging system for the prevention and treatment of venous leg ulcers.


 



2017-02-21
HARTMANN expands wound care portfolio with silicone bordered foam dressing
February 21, 2017, Rock Hill, SC – HARTMANN, a leading provider of wound care, compression and adult incontinence solutions, today announced the launch of PROXIMEL™, a five-layer silicone bordered foam dressing designed to promote a moist healing environment, manage wound exudate, enhance patient comfort and reduce the risk of pressure ulcers. PROXIMEL offers clinicians a new range of silicone bordered foam dressings to assist with the treatment of pressure ulcers, venous leg ulcers and chronic wounds.


